1
00:00:01,380 --> 00:00:05,050
[Episode 10: The soul has cell memories]

2
00:00:04,100 --> 00:00:07,430
Maybe this is the consequence
of wishing on a shooting star.

3
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,140
Everyone's going to forget me.

4
00:00:12,270 --> 00:00:14,540
Forget everything about He Xiangyong.

5
00:00:29,550 --> 00:00:30,200
Haowei.

6
00:00:31,230 --> 00:00:31,990
It's you.

7
00:00:32,830 --> 00:00:33,830
You're running?

8
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:35,550
Morning, Uncle Hua.

9
00:00:35,730 --> 00:00:36,460
Morning.

10
00:00:38,730 --> 00:00:39,630
Uncle Hua.

11
00:00:40,330 --> 00:00:41,410
I want to ask you something.

12
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:43,040
How long have you been on this island?

13
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,130
Over ten years.

14
00:00:44,190 --> 00:00:45,020
Why do you ask?

15
00:00:49,690 --> 00:00:50,630
Tell me,

16
00:00:51,360 --> 00:00:52,280
is it true that there's a legend
on this island

17
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,590
about shooting stars granting wishes?

18
00:01:39,670 --> 00:01:42,770
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

19
00:01:42,880 --> 00:01:44,250
How about one more?

20
00:01:44,270 --> 00:01:45,240
Dudu, here.

21
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:46,229
One more.

22
00:01:50,289 --> 00:01:51,490
Good morning, Mr. He.

23
00:01:51,860 --> 00:01:52,420
Good morning.

24
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,860
Why are you up so early?

25
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,560
Xiaoyou woke me up early this morning

26
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,900
and said he wanted to make me breakfast.

27
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,630
Have some fish porridge I made.

28
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:00,430
Isn't fish porridge hard to make?

29
00:02:00,430 --> 00:02:02,030
How do you know how to cook it?

30
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:03,670
It's not hard.

31
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,400
I used to make it a lot.

32
00:02:08,009 --> 00:02:09,150
My dad says

33
00:02:10,220 --> 00:02:11,670
fish porridge is the best cure

34
00:02:11,670 --> 00:02:12,810
for a hangover.

35
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:15,050
Your dad knows his stuff.

36
00:02:15,050 --> 00:02:15,990
Just like me.

37
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:17,550
I also like having some fish porridge

38
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:18,610
after a few drinks.

39
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:21,590
Here, Mr. He.

40
00:02:21,590 --> 00:02:22,290
Wait.

41
00:02:22,590 --> 00:02:23,320
So last night,

42
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,180
you two were drinking without me?

43
00:02:26,760 --> 00:02:28,160
We'll invite you next time.

44
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,760
Try the fish porridge first.

45
00:02:29,990 --> 00:02:31,360
That's not very nice.

46
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,230
Thank you.

47
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:34,070
Dudu, here.

48
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:38,940
Thank you.

49
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,150
This is so delicious.

50
00:02:47,150 --> 00:02:48,010
Of course it is.

51
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:49,620
It's a secret family recipe.

52
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:52,020
You can open a restaurant with this.

53
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:58,420
What's wrong?

54
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,690
You don't like it?

55
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,170
It's so good.

56
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:06,550
I feel like
I've had this somewhere before.

57
00:03:09,700 --> 00:03:10,670
Glad you like it.

58
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,340
If you ever feel like eating it,

59
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,310
just let me know.

60
00:03:13,610 --> 00:03:14,770
I'll make it for you.

61
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:21,850
Mr. He, do you want some eggs?

62
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:23,500
Thank you.

63
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,530
Thank you.

64
00:03:28,660 --> 00:03:29,520
Have some more.

65
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:36,460
This fish porridge is great,

66
00:03:37,500 --> 00:03:39,430
but it's still missing something.

67
00:03:40,630 --> 00:03:42,490
I'll take you somewhere tomorrow

68
00:03:42,530 --> 00:03:44,660
and show you how to make it even better.

69
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,130
Dudu, here.

70
00:03:53,940 --> 00:03:55,440
It's delicious. Try it.

71
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:56,520
Good boy.

72
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,310
Hamaguchi Soukai.

73
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:26,340
Get up.

74
00:04:26,580 --> 00:04:27,650
Get up.

75
00:04:28,110 --> 00:04:29,280
Hamaguchi Soukai.

76
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,450
Get up.

77
00:04:30,780 --> 00:04:31,950
Hamaguchi Soukai.

78
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,720
Good morning.

79
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,420
Good morning.

80
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:41,159
Can you go get Hamaguchi Soukai for me?

81
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,040
Okay.

82
00:04:43,659 --> 00:04:44,620
Thank you.

83
00:04:55,200 --> 00:04:56,170
Li Wanzhe.

84
00:04:57,409 --> 00:04:58,140
Good morning.

85
00:04:58,140 --> 00:04:58,940
Good morning.

86
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,180
You're up early.

87
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,010
Can you take a day off today?

88
00:05:03,190 --> 00:05:04,130
Why?

89
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:06,060
Come to the main island with me.

90
00:05:06,750 --> 00:05:07,680
What do you want?

91
00:05:07,790 --> 00:05:08,790
Stop asking so many questions.

92
00:05:08,790 --> 00:05:09,990
Are you coming or not?

93
00:05:10,990 --> 00:05:11,990
No way.

94
00:05:11,990 --> 00:05:13,660
Just go home and get some rest.

95
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:14,730
Get some sleep.

96
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,860
No.

97
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:17,230
It has to be today.

98
00:05:17,860 --> 00:05:18,900
Hey.

99
00:05:22,430 --> 00:05:23,330
Hamaguchi Soukai,

100
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:24,700
get up already!

101
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,840
Look at the time!

102
00:05:27,170 --> 00:05:27,970
You've slept long enough!

103
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:30,100
It's time to get up, Hamaguchi Soukai!

104
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:31,740
Hamaguchi Soukai!

105
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,159
Hamaguchi...

106
00:05:34,310 --> 00:05:36,210
Do you know what time it is?
Don't I need to sleep?

107
00:05:36,210 --> 00:05:37,820
It's time to wake up, Ying.

108
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,260
Ouch!

109
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,450
Get out.

110
00:05:42,420 --> 00:05:44,090
Keep your voice down.

111
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:46,020
No, I'm being loud.

112
00:05:46,820 --> 00:05:48,030
Hamaguchi Soukai.

113
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:50,190
You were born on January 10th, 1998.

114
00:05:50,190 --> 00:05:51,360
You're a Scorpio.

115
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,630
Your blood type is AB.

116
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,200
Your favorite food is plums.

117
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,530
And you hate mushrooms.

118
00:05:55,909 --> 00:05:57,370
Your biggest dream is to travel the world.

119
00:05:57,370 --> 00:05:58,300
You want to go to Antarctica.

120
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,230
And you said I was your whole world!

121
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,410
Your whole world...

122
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:04,040
You also said your favorite thing about me

123
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,040
was how much I cared about my family.

124
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:07,380
You like my cute eyes

125
00:06:07,380 --> 00:06:08,550
and my tall nose.

126
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:10,840
You bought me so many things to eat.

127
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:12,710
You got me concert tickets.

128
00:06:13,380 --> 00:06:15,090
You fought for me.

129
00:06:15,520 --> 00:06:15,950
You...

130
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,920
You even stole my first kiss!

131
00:06:19,840 --> 00:06:21,140
Stop making things up.

132
00:06:21,380 --> 00:06:22,550
I'm not!

133
00:06:23,490 --> 00:06:25,660
We've really been through a lot together.

134
00:06:25,660 --> 00:06:26,760
But I don't know why

135
00:06:26,930 --> 00:06:28,130
you've forgotten it all.

136
00:06:28,130 --> 00:06:29,330
I really hope

137
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:31,870
you can celebrate my birthday
with me again

138
00:06:31,870 --> 00:06:32,800
and that we can

139
00:06:33,140 --> 00:06:34,540
pick up where we left off.

140
00:06:34,870 --> 00:06:35,970
Please!

141
00:06:37,650 --> 00:06:39,280
Alright, go.

142
00:06:39,300 --> 00:06:41,690
I'll talk to the captain
and get you the day off.

143
00:06:41,690 --> 00:06:43,350
Okay, I'm going back to sleep.

144
00:06:44,480 --> 00:06:45,550
Go.

145
00:06:45,550 --> 00:06:47,220
You go. I'm going to bed.

146
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:48,350
So noisy.

147
00:06:52,590 --> 00:06:53,360
Okay.

148
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:54,659
Wait for me.

149
00:06:59,950 --> 00:07:00,740
Be quick.

150
00:07:08,540 --> 00:07:10,400
The fish you pick depends on the dish.

151
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,300
If you're making a banquet dish,

152
00:07:12,330 --> 00:07:13,580
go for the large deep-sea fish.

153
00:07:13,580 --> 00:07:14,710
They're over there.

154
00:07:14,940 --> 00:07:17,070
But for everyday cooking,

155
00:07:17,180 --> 00:07:18,550
like pan-frying, boiling,
stir-frying, or deep-frying,

156
00:07:18,550 --> 00:07:19,780
this is your section.

157
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:20,820
Hey, kid.

158
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,950
Playing with ice? Aren't you cold?

159
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:23,610
Li.

160
00:07:24,090 --> 00:07:24,590
Hi.

161
00:07:24,590 --> 00:07:25,450
Hello.

162
00:07:25,720 --> 00:07:26,620
I'd like to buy some fish.

163
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:27,390
Sure.

164
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:29,260
Do you know how to pick fish?

165
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:29,950
No.

166
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,430
Okay, look.

167
00:07:33,730 --> 00:07:35,470
Look at this one.

168
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,220
When you're picking fish,

169
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:38,670
the first thing to check is the eyes.

170
00:07:38,670 --> 00:07:40,970
They should be clear and bright.

171
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:43,710
The gills should be red.

172
00:07:44,280 --> 00:07:45,280
And the scales

173
00:07:45,780 --> 00:07:46,840
should be intact.

174
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:48,610
Press the belly.

175
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:50,980
It should feel firm and springy.

176
00:07:51,610 --> 00:07:53,610
Here, smell it. Does it smell fishy?

177
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:54,940
No.

178
00:07:54,990 --> 00:07:56,050
Then buy it quickly.

179
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:56,990
Li, this one.

180
00:07:56,990 --> 00:07:57,390
Okay.

181
00:07:57,390 --> 00:07:58,060
Clean it for me.

182
00:07:58,060 --> 00:07:58,820
I'll come back for it later.

183
00:07:58,820 --> 00:07:59,620
Okay.

184
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:04,430
Sir, what do you have today?

185
00:08:04,430 --> 00:08:05,360
Salmon heads,

186
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,700
shrimp, and yellow croakers.

187
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:07,630
These shrimp are huge.

188
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,430
The salmon heads are beautiful.

189
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,170
Look.

190
00:08:10,170 --> 00:08:10,870
Look.

191
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:12,200
Fresh red.

192
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:13,140
See?

193
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:14,240
So beautiful.

194
00:08:14,240 --> 00:08:15,270
I'll take another look around.

195
00:08:15,270 --> 00:08:16,570
Thank you.

196
00:08:19,340 --> 00:08:20,080
This must be your first time

197
00:08:20,080 --> 00:08:21,410
at a fish market, right?

198
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:25,650
My dad used to ask me
to come to the fish market with him.

199
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:26,980
But I always said no.

200
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:30,010
After a few times, he stopped asking.

201
00:08:31,490 --> 00:08:34,630
Now I kind of wish
I could go with him every day.

202
00:08:35,090 --> 00:08:36,230
Then do it if you want to.

203
00:08:36,230 --> 00:08:37,650
You can't just keep thinking about it.

204
00:08:37,650 --> 00:08:40,450
If all you do is think,
you'll never actually do it.

205
00:08:45,150 --> 00:08:47,350
You and your dad had a fight, didn't you?

206
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,010
Not exactly.

207
00:08:52,110 --> 00:08:53,660
But we used to argue a lot.

208
00:08:54,580 --> 00:08:56,570
We're too similar.

209
00:08:57,630 --> 00:08:59,160
We both care about each other,

210
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:01,020
but neither of us would back down.

211
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:08,180
Your dad already backed down.

212
00:09:08,510 --> 00:09:10,170
You just haven't realized it.

213
00:09:13,650 --> 00:09:15,610
Didn't he ask you
to come to the fish market with him?

214
00:09:15,610 --> 00:09:18,140
That was his way
of trying to get closer to you.

215
00:09:18,900 --> 00:09:19,940
Sometimes,

216
00:09:20,240 --> 00:09:22,240
men don't say much.

217
00:09:23,270 --> 00:09:25,580
Your dad brought you
to the place he knows best

218
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:27,840
because he wanted you to understand him.

219
00:09:30,210 --> 00:09:31,320
Maybe,

220
00:09:31,950 --> 00:09:32,980
he just wanted you to see

221
00:09:32,980 --> 00:09:34,520
those words up there.

222
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,870
[Caution: Wet Floor]

223
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:38,560
What do you mean?

224
00:09:42,830 --> 00:09:44,700
When you were little and learning to walk,

225
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:45,900
I'm sure your dad was there for you,

226
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,430
worried you might get hurt.

227
00:09:47,630 --> 00:09:49,030
Now that you've grown up,

228
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:51,600
you have your own path to walk.

229
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,170
You don't need your dad
by your side anymore.

230
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:56,370
But he still worries you might get hurt.

231
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:02,990
I'm not good enough.

232
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:06,040
I always let him down.

233
00:10:11,310 --> 00:10:13,310
What do you mean, "not good enough"?

234
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:17,190
What does "good" even mean?

235
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,160
When a family is together,

236
00:10:22,570 --> 00:10:24,070
all that really matters

237
00:10:24,070 --> 00:10:25,940
is peace, good health,

238
00:10:25,940 --> 00:10:27,670
and love for each other.

239
00:10:30,580 --> 00:10:31,680
Listen.

240
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:33,110
Go home and tell your dad

241
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:34,550
that you love him.

242
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,880
Trust me,

243
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:37,210
he'll be thrilled,

244
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,880
feeling like he's succeeded as a father.

245
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,180
Tomorrow, I bet he'll go run
for village chief.

246
00:10:40,180 --> 00:10:41,250
Mark my words.

247
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:43,420
Li, is my fish ready?

248
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:44,620
Yes.

249
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:45,580
Dad.

250
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:48,870
I love you.

251
00:10:49,330 --> 00:10:50,230
Go tell your dad.

252
00:10:50,230 --> 00:10:51,530
Why are you telling me?

253
00:10:51,530 --> 00:10:52,260
How much?

254
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:54,460
Two hundred. Okay, here.

255
00:10:55,900 --> 00:10:57,030
Alright, thanks.

256
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:59,050
Just let me practice.

257
00:11:00,500 --> 00:11:01,350
I love you.

258
00:11:01,370 --> 00:11:02,340
Stop it.

259
00:11:02,340 --> 00:11:03,540
I've got goosebumps all over.

260
00:11:03,540 --> 00:11:04,380
Here, two hundred.

261
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:05,680
Li, he says he loves you.

262
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:06,940
Go tell her.

263
00:11:07,280 --> 00:11:08,110
Bye, kid.

264
00:11:08,110 --> 00:11:08,750
Bye.

265
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:09,910
Bye. See you next time.

266
00:11:09,910 --> 00:11:11,280
Okay, see you.

267
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:12,820
You're the best.

268
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:14,220
I didn't expect the fish market
to be so small

269
00:11:14,220 --> 00:11:15,320
and so empty.

270
00:11:43,650 --> 00:11:45,080
What are you looking for?

271
00:11:45,670 --> 00:11:46,820
I can help you find it.

272
00:11:46,820 --> 00:11:48,790
I'm looking for Chocola BB Plus.

273
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:50,920
My mom specifically asked me
to get it for her

274
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:52,520
while I'm here on the main island.

275
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:54,830
Why does your mom
specifically want this one?

276
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:55,730
She says

277
00:11:55,730 --> 00:11:58,500
it's a really popular product
imported straight from Japan.

278
00:11:58,500 --> 00:12:00,400
It's got a B-complex formula

279
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,530
with vitamins B2, B6, and B1.

280
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,600
It helps with nutrition
and overall health.

281
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,800
Most importantly, the pills are tiny.

282
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:07,200
They're easy to swallow.

283
00:12:07,740 --> 00:12:08,570
My mom also says

284
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:10,310
it's made by a well-known
Japanese company,

285
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:11,640
so the quality is guaranteed.

286
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,110
She's been taking it every day lately,

287
00:12:13,110 --> 00:12:14,550
and her skin's been looking great.

288
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:15,610
She even told me to take it with her

289
00:12:15,610 --> 00:12:17,540
so we could stay healthy together.

290
00:12:18,350 --> 00:12:19,280
Also,

291
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,500
I think you could take it with us too.

292
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:22,340
Me?

293
00:12:23,820 --> 00:12:24,620
Why?

294
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:28,530
I just thought,
since you've been busy with work lately,

295
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:31,100
you seem a little worn out.

296
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,500
Are you saying I look bad?

297
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,230
I'm not.

298
00:12:36,230 --> 00:12:37,760
I'm just worried about you.

299
00:12:46,810 --> 00:12:48,080
I see.

300
00:12:48,430 --> 00:12:50,060
This is your way of flirting with me,
right?

301
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:51,360
Don't be ridiculous.

302
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:53,680
I'm just giving you some friendly advice.

303
00:12:53,680 --> 00:12:55,290
Try being less obvious next time.

304
00:12:55,290 --> 00:12:56,420
I'm not flirting...

305
00:12:58,090 --> 00:12:59,550
I'm not flirting with you.

306
00:12:59,620 --> 00:13:02,330
I'm trying to help you remember
why you fell for me.

307
00:13:02,330 --> 00:13:03,730
But listening to you now,

308
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:06,050
it sounds like you're the one into me.

309
00:13:06,830 --> 00:13:08,470
That's just because
you were crazy about me back then.

310
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:09,230
You were so sincere,
it even moved heaven.

311
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:10,630
That's why I fell for you.

312
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:12,400
Fine, I get it.

313
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:13,940
Whatever you say.

314
00:13:14,190 --> 00:13:15,490
Hamaguchi Soukai.

315
00:13:15,850 --> 00:13:17,220
You brat.

316
00:13:18,050 --> 00:13:18,820
Hama-chan.

317
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,240
What are you laughing at?

318
00:13:20,540 --> 00:13:22,780
I didn't expect you to shop at Matsukiyo.

319
00:13:22,780 --> 00:13:23,650
Of course I do.

320
00:13:23,810 --> 00:13:25,280
It's a famous Japanese drugstore.

321
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,680
You think I'm some kind of
country bumpkin?

322
00:13:34,560 --> 00:13:35,560
Do you know this?

323
00:13:37,230 --> 00:13:39,690
It's their own brand.
It's cheap and useful.

324
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:44,580
Of course I do.

325
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,530
I'm warning you.

326
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:47,230
I've tried everything here.

327
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:56,580
Look at this.

328
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:59,320
So cute.

329
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:03,710
Shopping with you is no fun at all.

330
00:14:05,330 --> 00:14:06,730
This looks good on you.

331
00:14:06,750 --> 00:14:07,420
How is it?

332
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:08,520
Not bad.

333
00:14:09,290 --> 00:14:10,160
Let's go.

334
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:17,900
Why the long face about shopping?

335
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:21,260
[Pretty]

336
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:21,430
Isn't it pretty?

337
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:37,050
Well, sausage.

338
00:14:37,050 --> 00:14:38,360
Fried sausage with blood sausage.

339
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,120
I'm telling you, you have to try it.

340
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:42,050
Or we can get some sugarcane juice.

341
00:14:42,070 --> 00:14:43,340
Sugar lane juice?

342
00:14:45,170 --> 00:14:46,110
Hello.

343
00:14:46,340 --> 00:14:47,710
Can I get a mixed one?

344
00:14:47,730 --> 00:14:48,770
Okay. Are you having it now?

345
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:49,130
Yes.

346
00:14:49,130 --> 00:14:49,500
Okay.

347
00:14:49,530 --> 00:14:50,970
Here, this one just came out fresh.

348
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:51,940
It's so pretty.

349
00:14:51,940 --> 00:14:52,870
Okay, thank you.

350
00:14:53,540 --> 00:14:54,000
Thank you.

351
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:54,540
Okay, thank you.

352
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:54,940
Bye.

353
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:55,410
Bye.

354
00:14:55,810 --> 00:14:57,170
Okay, thank you.

355
00:14:57,170 --> 00:14:58,840
Thank you.

356
00:14:58,840 --> 00:14:59,380
Bye.

357
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:00,210
Thank you.

358
00:15:00,710 --> 00:15:02,360
Chicken feet.
You've never had chicken feet?

359
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,890
Chicken feet. Chicken feet!

360
00:15:03,890 --> 00:15:04,760
Chicken feet?

361
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:05,920
He's never had them. He's Japanese.

362
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:06,680
He's never tried them.

363
00:15:06,680 --> 00:15:07,620
Yes.

364
00:15:07,820 --> 00:15:08,520
Thank you.

365
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,920
Come on. Smell it.

366
00:15:10,420 --> 00:15:11,560
Hello.

367
00:15:15,230 --> 00:15:16,390
Hurry.

368
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:17,700
What are you talking about?
I can't understand you.

369
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,330
No!

370
00:15:18,330 --> 00:15:19,100
Hurry!

371
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,130
This looks so ugly on me.

372
00:15:20,130 --> 00:15:22,730
No, it doesn't.
You picked such cool glasses yourself.

373
00:15:22,730 --> 00:15:23,730
Hold on.

374
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:27,150
Cool.

375
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:37,350
It stinks.

376
00:15:37,780 --> 00:15:39,720
The stinkier, the better.

377
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:44,870
You have to take a bite.

378
00:15:46,790 --> 00:15:47,790
Hurry.

379
00:15:50,410 --> 00:15:51,070
Otherwise,

380
00:15:51,310 --> 00:15:52,180
have some chicken feet instead.

381
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:53,640
Chicken feet don't stink.

382
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,960
You're turning down everything.

383
00:15:58,170 --> 00:15:58,870
Xiaotian,

384
00:15:58,940 --> 00:16:00,490
I've been eating
at that fish ball shop for ten years,

385
00:16:00,490 --> 00:16:02,100
and it still tastes the same.

386
00:16:02,130 --> 00:16:03,460
Yes, it's amazing.

387
00:16:03,770 --> 00:16:04,580
It's delicious.

388
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:05,710
Or have some drinks.

389
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,530
What are you looking at?

390
00:16:15,550 --> 00:16:17,150
-Let's just eat. -What?

391
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:19,460
I'm sorry.

392
00:16:19,460 --> 00:16:20,260
Sorry.

393
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:22,170
It's our first time traveling here.

394
00:16:22,170 --> 00:16:23,060
And he's Japanese.

395
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:24,030
So his Chinese

396
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:25,790
isn't very good.

397
00:16:26,070 --> 00:16:27,980
But your food is amazing.

398
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,860
I bought way too much
and can't finish it all.

399
00:16:29,860 --> 00:16:31,330
Here, it's on me.

400
00:16:32,170 --> 00:16:33,940
Why are you giving them our food?

401
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,230
Stop.

402
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:36,710
Stop talking.

403
00:16:36,960 --> 00:16:38,760
Why are you sharing it with them?

404
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:40,560
Shut up.

405
00:16:40,580 --> 00:16:41,480
Come on, let's go.

406
00:16:41,480 --> 00:16:43,740
Why are you suddenly speaking Japanese?

407
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:44,830
What are you doing?

408
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:45,950
Let's go.

409
00:16:47,310 --> 00:16:48,410
Sorry.

410
00:16:49,590 --> 00:16:51,290
Why did you suddenly speak Japanese?

411
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:52,690
That little punk.

412
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:54,490
I'm getting pissed off for no reason.

413
00:16:54,490 --> 00:16:56,730
I don't know why, but the more
I look at him, the more I want to hit him.

414
00:16:56,730 --> 00:16:58,270
Boss, my face hurts

415
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,620
when I see him.

416
00:16:59,660 --> 00:17:00,630
-And I don't know why. -Your face hurts?

417
00:17:00,630 --> 00:17:02,890
Sounds like your ass needs to get kicked.

418
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:11,260
We've had everything we wanted to eat

419
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:13,260
and done everything we wanted to do.

420
00:17:14,410 --> 00:17:16,050
So why did you bring me

421
00:17:16,790 --> 00:17:18,190
to the main island today?

422
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,050
You want to know?

423
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,790
Promise me three things first.

424
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:29,870
Then I'll tell you.

425
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:40,230
First,

426
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:43,630
you can never give up your dream
of becoming a sailor.

427
00:17:44,410 --> 00:17:46,340
I wasn't going to give it up anyway.

428
00:17:46,340 --> 00:17:47,210
That's great.

429
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:48,650
Second,

430
00:17:49,150 --> 00:17:50,950
whatever danger you face in the future,

431
00:17:50,950 --> 00:17:52,360
you have to protect yourself first.

432
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:53,960
Only then can you protect me.

433
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:01,690
Third,

434
00:18:04,130 --> 00:18:05,660
whenever you hear the bell,

435
00:18:05,730 --> 00:18:07,060
you have to do what I say.

436
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:08,570
The bell again?

437
00:18:10,300 --> 00:18:11,500
You're the one who gave it to me.

438
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,220
You said

439
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:13,540
if I rang this bell,

440
00:18:13,540 --> 00:18:14,940
no matter where I was or what time it was,

441
00:18:14,940 --> 00:18:16,200
you would come find me.

442
00:18:16,740 --> 00:18:17,910
Anyway, you forgot it later.

443
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:19,110
After that, I just rang the bell...

444
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:19,940
I promise.

445
00:18:21,770 --> 00:18:22,580
I promise you.

446
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,220
Good.

447
00:18:28,850 --> 00:18:29,910
Congratulations.

448
00:18:30,070 --> 00:18:31,410
Hamaguchi Soukai.

449
00:18:31,630 --> 00:18:33,760
I ate the stinky tofu and chicken feet.

450
00:18:33,860 --> 00:18:34,490
I, Li Wanzhe...

451
00:18:34,490 --> 00:18:35,470
I know.

452
00:18:38,310 --> 00:18:40,270
I know you brought me to the main island

453
00:18:40,270 --> 00:18:42,270
because you wanted to confess to me.

454
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:49,350
You like me, don't you?

455
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:52,770
Well,

456
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,210
I like you too.

457
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:57,650
So...

458
00:18:59,730 --> 00:19:00,930
let's go out on a date.

459
00:19:04,220 --> 00:19:04,810
Okay.

460
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:08,160
I knew it.

461
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,790
You liked me first.

462
00:19:19,050 --> 00:19:19,860
That's it?

463
00:19:26,620 --> 00:19:28,080
I brought all these props for nothing.

464
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:28,980
Look, I even brought this.

465
00:19:28,980 --> 00:19:30,780
I didn't even get to use it. Look.

466
00:19:31,180 --> 00:19:31,980
And this.

467
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:32,940
Bam, bam, bam.

468
00:19:32,970 --> 00:19:34,070
It's gone.

469
00:20:01,270 --> 00:20:02,840
Wait, I'm not done yet.

470
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:07,440
I also brought a fairy stick.

471
00:20:08,550 --> 00:20:10,790
I thought, if…

472
00:20:11,050 --> 00:20:12,490
if my confession went well…

473
00:20:12,490 --> 00:20:13,380
Wait, not my confession.

474
00:20:13,380 --> 00:20:14,910
You're the one who likes me.

475
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:16,050
Yes, you like me.

476
00:20:24,610 --> 00:20:25,870
Li Wanzhe.

477
00:20:27,260 --> 00:20:28,960
I like you!

478
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,580
I like you!

479
00:20:39,020 --> 00:20:40,450
It's so hot!

480
00:20:42,330 --> 00:20:43,500
Here, take this.

481
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:45,260
-Hurry up. -Don't push it to me.

482
00:20:45,920 --> 00:20:48,590
Draw a circle.

483
00:21:28,710 --> 00:21:30,170
I can tell you're not professional

484
00:21:30,170 --> 00:21:32,370
from the way you're holding that drill.

485
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:35,510
It's broken.

486
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:36,860
No, it's not.

487
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,650
You're drilling the wrong way.

488
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:42,240
I know, okay?

489
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:44,700
See? It's in.

490
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,750
How long are you going to keep drilling?

491
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,470
I'm going to sleep. Don't disturb me.

492
00:21:47,470 --> 00:21:49,130
It won't kill you to skip a nap.

493
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:50,350
I'm going fishing tonight.

494
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,490
It's very important, you know?

495
00:21:51,490 --> 00:21:53,380
-You can go night fishing any day. -Hello.

496
00:21:53,380 --> 00:21:54,610
Is anyone here?

497
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:55,330
-We've got a guest. -I have a reservation.

498
00:21:55,330 --> 00:21:55,970
Yes!

499
00:21:56,690 --> 00:21:57,320
I'll go.

500
00:21:57,930 --> 00:21:59,590
I'll be right back to help you.

501
00:22:01,430 --> 00:22:02,300
Keep it down.

502
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,500
There's a guest out there.
How loud are you trying to be?

503
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,640
This is just how it sounds.

504
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:05,570
Excuse me!

505
00:22:06,670 --> 00:22:07,370
Hello, sir.

506
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,800
Are you going to check in?

507
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:12,170
Chen Haowei?

508
00:22:13,730 --> 00:22:14,560
Mr. Lin.

509
00:22:14,840 --> 00:22:16,280
Why are you here?

510
00:22:16,650 --> 00:22:18,210
So you've opened a guesthouse?

511
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:19,810
Are you into real estate now?

512
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:21,180
No, I...

513
00:22:21,290 --> 00:22:22,290
I work here.

514
00:22:22,310 --> 00:22:23,350
You work here?

515
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:25,550
But all my money went down the drain.

516
00:22:26,160 --> 00:22:26,620
What do you think?

517
00:22:26,620 --> 00:22:28,350
Got any new investment advice?

518
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:30,060
You're my stock market jinx

519
00:22:30,060 --> 00:22:31,560
and my reverse indicator.

520
00:22:31,860 --> 00:22:32,430
Thanks to you,

521
00:22:32,430 --> 00:22:34,290
I got the chance to come fish here.

522
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,070
Just tell me.

523
00:22:36,210 --> 00:22:37,890
You've caused me so much trouble anyway.

524
00:22:37,890 --> 00:22:39,030
I've even shut down my company.

525
00:22:39,030 --> 00:22:40,160
I've checked you in.

526
00:22:40,290 --> 00:22:41,320
Thank you

527
00:22:41,340 --> 00:22:43,670
for teaching me that money means nothing.

528
00:22:45,210 --> 00:22:45,860
Come on.

529
00:22:45,950 --> 00:22:48,260
Tell me about your latest investments.

530
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,660
Chen Haowei,

531
00:22:50,780 --> 00:22:51,880
didn't I ask you to go shopping?

532
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:53,740
What are you doing standing here?

533
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:56,420
Sir, are you checking in?

534
00:22:57,050 --> 00:22:58,020
Wow, nice fishing rod.

535
00:22:58,020 --> 00:22:58,960
You like fishing too?

536
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,320
I'm a beginner.

537
00:23:00,320 --> 00:23:01,360
I never used to fish at all.

538
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:02,950
A beginner?
Then you've come to the right place.

539
00:23:02,950 --> 00:23:04,540
Our boss is really good at fishing.

540
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:05,380
Mr. He.

541
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:06,560
Mr. He.

542
00:23:06,650 --> 00:23:07,540
What?

543
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:10,200
This gentleman here
is also really into fishing.

544
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:11,700
Do you want to talk to him?

545
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,000
Do you like fishing?

546
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,040
I know how to fish.

547
00:23:16,320 --> 00:23:18,240
-Mr. He is amazing.
-This fishing rod is awesome.

548
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:19,070
Of course.

549
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:20,410
It cost me three houses.

550
00:23:20,410 --> 00:23:22,450
-It's that expensive?
-All thanks to a great employee.

551
00:23:22,450 --> 00:23:23,510
Come on, let's go inside

552
00:23:23,510 --> 00:23:24,310
and get you checked in.

553
00:23:24,310 --> 00:23:24,780
Thank you.

554
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:25,420
-Let me help you. -Mr. He.

555
00:23:25,420 --> 00:23:26,380
We'll go buy some bait.

556
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:27,510
Alright, off you go.

557
00:23:28,620 --> 00:23:29,750
Let me tell you something.

558
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:30,860
Here on Xingpu Island,

559
00:23:30,860 --> 00:23:32,590
we don't use hooks when we fish.

560
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:50,210
Mr. Lin

561
00:23:50,620 --> 00:23:53,280
must be the client
who lost all his money, right?

562
00:24:05,390 --> 00:24:07,890
Do you know why the sea is blue?

563
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:12,660
No.

564
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:15,610
Because the fish in the sea go,

565
00:24:15,750 --> 00:24:17,490
"blu-blu-blu."

566
00:24:22,210 --> 00:24:23,740
"Blu-blu-blu."

567
00:24:29,430 --> 00:24:30,960
Is it really that funny?

568
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:40,470
There you go.

569
00:24:42,290 --> 00:24:43,440
If you can laugh,

570
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:46,930
then remember
you're allowed to be angry too,

571
00:24:46,930 --> 00:24:47,910
and sad.

572
00:24:49,250 --> 00:24:50,980
Cry when you need to cry.

573
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:53,490
Laugh when you feel like laughing.

574
00:24:54,340 --> 00:24:55,690
We're not robots.

575
00:24:58,930 --> 00:25:00,500
You don't need to hide who you really are

576
00:25:00,500 --> 00:25:01,910
in front of me.

577
00:25:03,610 --> 00:25:05,410
No matter how the world changes,

578
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:07,840
as long as I'm still here,

579
00:25:09,620 --> 00:25:11,020
I'll always support you.

580
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:20,600
So,

581
00:25:21,430 --> 00:25:23,300
whenever we're in a bad mood,

582
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:24,730
we come here,

583
00:25:25,450 --> 00:25:26,780
face the ocean,

584
00:25:30,260 --> 00:25:31,120
close our eyes,

585
00:25:34,340 --> 00:25:35,470
and start counting.

586
00:25:35,850 --> 00:25:36,810
1, 4, 2.

587
00:25:37,510 --> 00:25:38,630
8, 5, 7.

588
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,900
Then open your eyes slowly,

589
00:25:48,930 --> 00:25:50,990
and all your worries will disappear.

590
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:54,660
You remember?

591
00:26:01,730 --> 00:26:02,930
I had a dream about it.

592
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:10,480
That's okay.

593
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:13,130
Maybe if you keep dreaming,

594
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:15,480
your memories will get clearer
and clearer.

595
00:26:15,480 --> 00:26:17,340
And then you'll remember who I am.

596
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:21,440
Anyway, I believe

597
00:26:21,930 --> 00:26:23,530
even if memories fade,

598
00:26:24,010 --> 00:26:25,610
feelings leave their marks.

599
00:26:26,450 --> 00:26:27,710
Just like He Xiangyong

600
00:26:27,710 --> 00:26:29,150
showing up in your dream.

601
00:26:33,540 --> 00:26:34,780
So you think

602
00:26:36,770 --> 00:26:38,900
my dreams are the marks of my feelings?

603
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:42,550
You remember those numbers.

604
00:26:43,330 --> 00:26:45,100
That counts as proof, right?

605
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:24,310
That's...

606
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,380
my sketchbook.

607
00:27:30,170 --> 00:27:31,340
Can I have a look?

608
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:34,980
Sure.

609
00:28:01,160 --> 00:28:02,590
I don't know why,

610
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:04,760
but when I woke up,

611
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:08,130
everything connected to me
had disappeared.

612
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:11,300
The sketchbook was the only thing left.

613
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:48,060
What's wrong?

614
00:28:53,580 --> 00:28:55,310
A big oval,

615
00:28:56,400 --> 00:28:58,240
add a spiral in the middle,

616
00:28:58,560 --> 00:29:00,600
then 4 boomerangs.

617
00:29:00,620 --> 00:29:01,620
Boomerangs?

618
00:29:01,650 --> 00:29:02,370
Yes.

619
00:29:04,090 --> 00:29:05,560
And most importantly...

620
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:06,760
a big head.

621
00:29:06,790 --> 00:29:08,830
Big head and little tail.

622
00:29:09,230 --> 00:29:09,930
Easy, right?

623
00:29:09,930 --> 00:29:11,830
Big head and little tail.

624
00:29:14,360 --> 00:29:15,230
You...

625
00:29:21,330 --> 00:29:22,500
I don't know why,

626
00:29:24,870 --> 00:29:26,730
but I have this feeling inside...

627
00:29:26,740 --> 00:29:28,080
I want to hug you

628
00:29:28,340 --> 00:29:29,550
and comfort you.

629
00:29:37,230 --> 00:29:38,530
Why?

630
00:29:42,930 --> 00:29:43,710
I'm sorry.

631
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,900
I've asked Uncle Hua about it.

632
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,150
He made a wish too,

633
00:29:50,270 --> 00:29:52,670
and he also experienced memory confusion.

634
00:29:58,780 --> 00:29:59,710
Uncle Hua?

635
00:30:03,900 --> 00:30:10,290
[Epilogue]

636
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:10,320
You mean Xiaoyou made a wish too?

637
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:14,650
What do you mean, "too"?

638
00:30:14,730 --> 00:30:16,530
Did anyone else also make a wish?

639
00:30:19,810 --> 00:30:21,210
After my wish came true,

640
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:24,580
I never went back to the main island.

641
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:27,340
I've stayed on Xingpu Island ever since,

642
00:30:30,310 --> 00:30:33,510
letting these little boats
carry my grief and apologies.

643
00:30:37,890 --> 00:30:38,690
Uncle Hua,

644
00:30:39,750 --> 00:30:40,880
your little patient

645
00:30:41,030 --> 00:30:42,500
would never want you

646
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:44,980
to carry this guilt
for the rest of your life.

647
00:30:46,980 --> 00:30:48,810
You came to me for help,

648
00:30:49,300 --> 00:30:51,360
and now you're the one comforting me.

649
00:30:52,060 --> 00:30:52,960
It's fine.

650
00:30:53,990 --> 00:30:55,260
Some things are just

651
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:56,630
easier said than done.

652
00:30:57,720 --> 00:30:59,720
Anyway, back to what we were saying.

653
00:31:00,640 --> 00:31:01,300
By the way,

654
00:31:01,300 --> 00:31:02,760
lately I keep feeling like

655
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:06,730
my memories are getting a bit blurry.

656
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:09,020
They feel like dreams,

657
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:11,780
but they also feel like reality.

658
00:31:14,120 --> 00:31:15,820
Doesn't that confuse you?

659
00:31:16,670 --> 00:31:18,230
How do you tell what was a dream

660
00:31:18,230 --> 00:31:20,200
and what actually happened?

661
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,690
Have you heard of

662
00:31:21,860 --> 00:31:22,590
cell memory

663
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:23,830
or body memory?

664
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,460
The theory suggests

665
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:30,520
that memories aren't
just stored in the brain, right?

666
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:31,280
Yes.

667
00:31:34,460 --> 00:31:36,630
Was there a table here before?

668
00:31:36,660 --> 00:31:37,960
Or a cabinet?

669
00:31:39,630 --> 00:31:41,230
Has it always been like this?

670
00:31:42,270 --> 00:31:43,730
Something feels off.

671
00:31:48,770 --> 00:31:50,630
Why did you cook so many rice cakes?

672
00:31:50,630 --> 00:31:52,430
Didn't you say he likes them?

673
00:31:53,270 --> 00:31:53,960
Who?

674
00:31:58,330 --> 00:31:58,940
Who?

675
00:32:01,480 --> 00:32:02,310
Well...

676
00:32:04,970 --> 00:32:07,900
This is so weird.
How come I suddenly can't remember?

677
00:32:08,950 --> 00:32:09,650
But still,

678
00:32:10,210 --> 00:32:11,340
this is just an unproven theory.

679
00:32:11,340 --> 00:32:13,540
There's no scientific evidence for it.

680
00:32:14,930 --> 00:32:17,790
How come you're even more
of a science nerd than I am?

681
00:32:17,890 --> 00:32:19,040
Let me tell you about this jar.

682
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:20,240
It was empty at first.

683
00:32:21,250 --> 00:32:22,420
Two nights ago, I couldn't sleep,

684
00:32:22,420 --> 00:32:23,880
so I decided to read a book.

685
00:32:24,050 --> 00:32:25,440
But somehow, out of nowhere,

686
00:32:25,440 --> 00:32:27,020
I started folding paper boats.

687
00:32:27,020 --> 00:32:29,220
Before I knew it, the whole jar was full.

688
00:32:29,570 --> 00:32:31,900
That's when I realized
the saying is true.

689
00:32:33,010 --> 00:32:35,480
The end of science is metaphysics.

690
00:32:38,750 --> 00:32:40,480
I think I've heard that before.

691
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:42,610
No wonder I feel like

692
00:32:42,610 --> 00:32:43,940
I can find answers here.

693
00:32:44,170 --> 00:32:46,100
Then you must have heard it before.

694
00:32:46,380 --> 00:32:48,040
Instead of being confused
by your memories,

695
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,450
you should trust your feelings.

696
00:32:49,450 --> 00:32:50,780
Feel it with your heart.

697
00:32:51,180 --> 00:32:52,710
Your heart won't lie to you.

698
00:32:55,150 --> 00:32:55,890
Got one!

699
00:33:22,950 --> 00:33:25,080
Since you chose to abandon He Xiangyong,

700
00:33:23,280 --> 00:33:28,080
[Next Episode]

701
00:33:25,620 --> 00:33:26,920
he won't come back then.

702
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:28,220
Once your wish starts to backfire,

703
00:33:28,220 --> 00:33:28,920
it'll be too late for regrets.

704
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:29,510
What do you want?

705
00:33:29,510 --> 00:33:31,750
Hama-chan wants to sail out
and see the world.

706
00:33:31,750 --> 00:33:33,480
He's going to sign a contract
with a deep-sea fleet.

707
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,750
Put me down!

708
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:36,260
Have you ever thought

709
00:33:36,260 --> 00:33:37,290
that maybe you don't deserve

710
00:33:37,290 --> 00:33:38,190
to live in this world?

711
00:33:38,190 --> 00:33:40,460
I have to find He Xiangyong to get better.
